{"id": "duc04-testb-42:16#47", "contents": "Exxon and Mobil, the nation's two largest oil companies, confirmed Friday that they were discussing a possible merger, and antitrust lawyers, industry analysts, and government officials predicted that any deal would require the sale of important large pieces of such a new corporate behemoth. Those divestitures would further reshape an industry already undergoing a broad transformation because of the low price of oil. The mergers and other corporate combinations are also beginning to create a new regulatory climate among antitrust officials, one that may prove particularly challenging to Exxon and Mobil."}
